Nigerian comedienne, Helen Paul, has been inducted as a fellow of the Chartered Institute of Local Government and Public Administration of Nigeria. This was revealed by media personality, Tope Mark-Odigie, who posted some pictures of the induction on her Facebook page on Thursday. Odigie wrote “I celebrate grace, grit and hard work. Congratulations, Dr. Helen Paul on your induction into the Chartered Institute of Local Government and Public Administration of Nigeria. “This woman is a bundle of talent and immense hard work. She has more certifications than I can count, and yet super humble. I celebrate you and I love you sister, you inspire us to be more. Keep growing.” Sharing pictures of the event, Helen Paul dedicated her new status to her husband. She wrote, “It’s a great honour to be a fellow of the Chartered Institute of Local Government and Public Administration of the Federal Republic of Nigeria. And I dedicate this to my husband Barrister Femi Bamisile LLB, LLM, MBA, MPA, ICSAN for always releasing me to achieve just like you. I love you always.” See photos below:  Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com